step_data.thought:
I'm now on the Categories page where I can edit existing product categories. Looking at the page, I can see I'm currently viewing the 'Default Category (ID: 2)' which is highlighted in the category tree on the left side of the page. 

To edit a product category, I need to select one of the subcategories from the tree. I can see there are several subcategories under the Default Category such as 'What's New', 'Women', 'Men', 'Gear', etc.

For this task, I'll choose one of the subcategories to edit. Let's select 'New Product Category (ID: 44)' which appears to be a custom category that might need editing.

I need to click on this category in the tree to select it and load its details for editing.
